name: proline dehydrogenase
classes: Acting on the CH-NH group of donors;
With a quinone or similar compound as acceptor
comment: A flavoprotein (FAD). The electrons from L-proline are transferred to the FAD cofactor, and from there to a quinone acceptor [3]. In many organisms, ranging from bacteria to mammals, proline is oxidized to glutamate in a two-step process involving this enzyme and EC 1.2.1.88, L-glutamate gamma-semialdehyde dehydrogenase. Both activities are carried out by the same enzyme in enterobacteria.

orthologs.K13821: RHH-type transcriptional regulator, proline utilization regulon repressor / proline dehydrogenase / delta 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase
